news.title: Capital gains deduction limit of Rs 10 crore to hurt luxury property deals
news.para: The move is also likely to impact redevelopment projects in high-value realty markets such as south Mumbai and a few localities in Delhi, said tax experts, although realty developers didn’t agree.

news.title: In Gujarat, stamp duty collection up 19% to Rs 8,769 crore in 2022
news.para: According to official data, the number of properties registered in 2022 in the state stood at 15,97,188, 11% higher than 14,29,607 properties registered in the preceding year.

news.title: Ambuja Cement, ACC say no shares pledged by promoter Adani group
news.para: In a joint statement to stock exchanges, Ambuja Cement Ltd and ACC Ltd termed as "misleading" reports of pledging of shares by the promoters as part of financing their acquisition.

news.title: Relief to flat buyers of stuck projects, Rs 101 crore recovered from builders: MahaRERA
news.para: Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) regularly passes orders against developers who have not delivered on projects and follows up on them by sending warrants for recoveries to district collectors, it said in a statement.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces' net profit increases by 37.17% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Mahindra Lifespaces' net consolidated income stood at Rs 198.14 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 494.66 per cent from Rs 33.32 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Asian Granito posts net loss of Rs 26.89 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: Asian Granito India's net consolidated income stood at Rs 406.07 crore in Q3 FY23, a dip of 7.31 per cent from Rs 438.09 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Blackstone REIT blocks investor withdrawals in January
news.para: BREIT said it fulfilled redemption requests of about $1.3 billion in January, representing 25% of the approximately $5.5 billion of the total withdrawal requests it had received during the month. The fulfilled withdrawal requests also represents 2% of the net asset value of fund, the firm said.

news.title: Sebi mulls regulatory framework for REITs, InvITs to issue depository receipts
news.para: Real Estate Investment Trusts (REITs) and Infrastructure Investment Trusts (InvITs) are set up as Business Trusts and hold and operate revenue-generating real estate or infrastructure assets, respectively. REITs and InvITs raise funds by issuing units to the public at large.

news.title: Kamdhenu's net profit increases by 83.36% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Kamdhenu's net consolidated income stood at Rs 183.16 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 22.61 per cent from Rs 149.38 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: HCC reports net loss of Rs 258.44 crore in Q3 FY23
news.para: HCC's net consolidated income stood at Rs 2,046.69 crore in Q3 FY23, a dip of 21.34 per cent from Rs 2,602.09 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Berger Paints' net profit dips 20.48% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Berger Paints' net consolidated income stood at Rs 2,704.47 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 5.39 per cent from Rs 2,566.22 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Cera Sanitaryware's net profit up 31.91% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Cera Sanitaryware's net consolidated income stood at Rs 471.06 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 20.06 per cent from Rs 392.35 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Aptus Value Housing Finance's net profit up 23.74% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Aptus Value Housing Finance's net consolidated income stood at Rs 294.80 crore in Q3 FY23, a dip of 36.39 per cent from Rs 216.31 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Godrej Properties' net profit up 44.54% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Godrej Properties' net consolidated income stood at Rs 404.58 crore in Q3 FY23, a dip of 13.35 per cent from Rs 466.91 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Chinese cities lower or scrap floor on mortgage rates to boost demand
news.para: The Chinese central bank on Jan. 6 said it was allowing some cities with home prices falling month-on-month and year-on-year for three consecutive months to cut or abolish the floor on mortgage rates for first-home buyers.
